# Architecture rules (editor-enforced)

Full rationale lives in `CLAUDE.md`. These are the constraints to apply while editing.

## Dependency direction (never violate)
- `api/` may import `logic`, `domain/model`, `common` — NEVER `data`.
- `logic/` may import `domain/*`, `common`, context-maps — NEVER `data` or `api`.
- `domain/model/` may import `common` ONLY — NEVER `@nestjs/*`, mongoose, or any framework.
- `data/` may import `domain/model`, `common`, mongoose — NEVER `api` or `logic`.
- Cross-domain access goes through a context map, never another domain's internals.

## Domain modeling
- Wrap EVERY non-primitive domain concept (IDs, states, enums, composites) in a Value Object.
- Aggregates: mutate via `this.assign('prop', value)`; emit events only via `this.addEvent(...)`.
- Never override the base `toObject()` — use a transformer in `data/`.
- Factories: `createNew()` (Created) vs `createFromExisting()` (Loaded).
- Throw typed errors (`ValidationError`, `NotFoundError`, `ConflictError`) — never `new Error()`.

## Application & data
- Interactors/handlers inject repository INTERFACES, never implementations.
- Persist aggregate + domain events atomically in `TransactionManager.withTransaction()`.
- Side-effects (queues, notifications, external calls) run AFTER the transaction commits.
- Repositories extend the base `Repository`, use Input/Output transformers, accept `ClientSession`.

## Transport
- Controllers: validate (`StrictValidationPipe`) + delegate. Zero business logic.
- Always apply `@UseFilters(NatsExceptionFilter | JetStreamExceptionFilter)`.
- Return response DTOs, never domain objects. DTOs live in `api/src/lib/{dtos,exchanges}/`.

## Imports
- Use `@supy/*` aliases, never relative paths across library boundaries.
- Order: side-effect → third-party → `@supy/*` → relative.

## Misc
- Store dates in UTC; convert to retailer `ianaTimeZone` for business logic only.
- No `any` without a justification comment. Scaffold new domains with the generator.
